<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/20738920-orinoco-womble-tidy-bag-and-all"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1406361683i/20738920._UX100_CR0,18,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/20738920-orinoco-womble-tidy-bag-and-all">Orinoco Womble (tidy bag and all)</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s from a song, &quot;Come all you fair and tender ladies, take warning how how you court your men...&quot; The song is about not letting your passions run aw<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's from a song, "Come all you fair and tender ladies, take warning how how you court your men..." The song is about not letting your passions run away with you, and particularly not believing the lines men spin to get women to have sex with them. "They're like a star on a summer morning, they first appear and then they're gone." <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
