    <a title="Antoinette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette"><img alt="Antoinette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1503842818p2/5328952.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2340396130?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Antoinette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Antoinette" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette">Antoinette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780330307987" href="/book/show/2242943.Fair_and_Tender_Ladies">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2340396130" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16165218631511549358">Ivy Rowe’s voice has been living in my mind since I started this book. When I wake at night, I hear her talking with her Virginia twang. She is certainly a memorable character.<br/><br/>Ivy loves to write letters- we learn about Ivy, her family,her loves and her life on the mountains. The letters are Ivy’s connection to the outside world. It made me yearn for the lost art of letter writing.<br/><br/>Ivy had a unique personality- high spirited, head strong, impetuous, caring, loving but also irresponsible. I am glad</span>
  <span id="freeText16165218631511549358" style="display:none">Ivy Rowe’s voice has been living in my mind since I started this book. When I wake at night, I hear her talking with her Virginia twang. She is certainly a memorable character.<br /><br />Ivy loves to write letters- we learn about Ivy, her family,her loves and her life on the mountains. The letters are Ivy’s connection to the outside world. It made me yearn for the lost art of letter writing.<br /><br />Ivy had a unique personality- high spirited, head strong, impetuous, caring, loving but also irresponsible. I am glad she wasn’t totally perfect, or else, who knows if I would have found her as believable.<br /><br />I totally enjoyed submerging myself in Ivy’s thoughts and words.<br /><br />“ A person can not afford to forget who they are or where they came from, or so I think, even when the remembering brings pain.”<br /><br />“ The true nature will come out whether or no, we have all got a true nature and we can hide it, it will pop out when you least expect it.”<br /><br />This is a book that I will definitely remember, with the unique voice that is Ivy Rowe. If you enjoy epistolary novels, then you will most definitely enjoy this one.<br /><br />Forgot to add my thanks to my GR friends- Candi and Cheri, whose reviews brought me to this book!! Loved the recommendation:)</span>
  <a data-text-id="16165218631511549358" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

